Caption: THE BALLOTS ARE NOW OPEN! If you are interested in being part of the ASU Executive Team for the 2024-2025 academic year now is your chance! The nomination period is open starting now, until Tuesday, May 21st at 11:59 P.M. 

If you have any questions about the roles or the election, please feel free to send us a message! We will also be answering any inquiries at the End of Year Barbecue taking place on May 16th at Downsview Park. 

The voting period will then take place from May 22-May 28th, with the winners announced on May 30th. 

Please fill out the Google Form linked below, as well as in our bio, for any and all positions you would like to run for! We would love to have you join us next year as a member of the team!

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScK5wB4BDxuSZ1vuKf0Ts-Zn3-RK8d4Wa-9N8V1KUAsxi_xmA/viewform?usp=sf_link

Don’t feel like running in an election? Fret not! You can always join us as a General Member and be involved in all the exciting events, without all the hard work. That form can also be found in our bio :)

Caption: Congratulations to everyone on finishing another academic year! The ASU and AAY have come together to throw the last great event of the year. 

Come join us for a barbecue at Downsview Park on Thursday, May 16th from 6:00 P.M. until sunrise do us part! There will be food, games, music and generally good vibes. Oh and did I mention FOOD???? Feel free to bring your own food, snacks, beverages, and barbecue items such as picnic blankets or frisbees as you see fit.

Caption: Thank you to everyone who joined us for our Legal Career Panel a few weeks ago. We were so happy to see you all there and hope that you found the event as enjoyable as we had hoped!

If you enjoyed the panel as an attendee and would like to see more events like these please let us know!

Caption: You might want to learn about Canada's first fully student-funded and student-developed satellite mission, HERON Mk. II. ✨⁠
⁠
On November 11, 2023, HERON Mk. II, a 3U CubeSat built by @uoft_aerospaceteam, soared into space aboard a @SpaceX #Falcon9 rocket. Witnessing the culmination of years of hard work, Benjamin Nero (UTIAS MASc candidate) shared the experience as HERON's mission manager as “surreal”. ⁠
⁠
This achievement involved over 100 students. Despite challenges, the team was undeterred to fulfill HERON Mk. II’s primary mission: to demonstrate UTAT’s radio communications capabilities, while secondary objectives are to include validating the structural, thermal, power, and computing system designs. 🛰️ ⁠
⁠
The journey continues with HERON's ground-breaking success paving the way for UTAT's next mission, FINCH, set to launch in late 2025. Learn more in our bio link. 🌐⁠
⁠
Photos courtesy of SpaceX and UTAT.⁠
⁠
#SpaceXLaunch #StudentInnovation #CubeSat #UTIAS #SpaceExploration #StudentAchievement
